---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do I own my Wix or Squarespace site?",
    a: "Not really. You own the words and images you put in, but the site itself lives on their platform and only works as long as you keep paying. You can't export it and run it somewhere else, and you don't get the underlying code. It's a rental; a nice one, but a rental.",
  },
  {
    q: "What happens to my website if I stop paying?",
    a: "On a builder like Wix or Squarespace, it goes dark; the pages, the forms, sometimes even the email tied to it. Customers who click your link hit a dead page. When you own your site outright, like the ones I build, it keeps running whether or not you ever pay another person, because the code and hosting are in your name.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can I move my website to a different developer?",
    a: "If you own the code, yes; you hand over the files and the new person picks up where the last one left off. If you're on a closed platform, usually no; you'd be starting from scratch. That's the whole reason owning the code matters: it keeps you free to walk away.",
  },
  {
    q: "What is \"code,\" in plain English?",
    a: "Code is the set of instructions that tells a web browser how to build your page; the text, the layout, the buttons, the whole thing. Think of it like the blueprints and materials for a house. When you own the code, you hold the blueprints, so you can hand them to any builder and they can work on your site. On a rented platform, you never get the blueprints; they stay locked inside that company.",
  },
  {
    q: "What is website hosting?",
    a: "Hosting is the space on the internet where your website actually lives, like renting the lot your building sits on so customers can come visit. Every website needs it. What matters is whose name the hosting is under: when I build your site, the hosting account is yours, so the site stays online even if you and I part ways.",
  },
  {
    q: "Who owns my domain name?",
    a: "Your domain (yourbusiness.com) should always be registered in your name, with your email and card on the account; never the developer's. If someone else holds your domain, they can hold your whole web presence hostage. Always check this one. It's the address customers find you at, and it should be yours.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Do You Own Your Website? (Wix vs. Custom)"
  description="Most small business owners don't actually own their website; they rent it. Here's what owning really means, how to check, and why it matters the day you want to leave."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": faqs.map((f) => ({
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": f.q,
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a },
      })),
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Do You Own Your Website?", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/do-you-own-your-website/" },
      ],
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />

  <main class="page">
    <article class="intro">
      <div class="intro__container">
        <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> Do You Own Your Website?
        </nav>
        <span class="overline">RENTING VS. OWNING</span>
        <h1 class="h1">Do You Own Your Website?</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Most business owners can't answer that, and they don't find out until the
          worst moment; a fee jumps, a developer disappears, or they try to move
          and learn they can't take anything with them. If your site is on Wix,
          Squarespace, or GoDaddy, here's the hard truth: you're renting it, not
          owning it.
        </p>
        <p class="body body--gold">
          Owning your website is simple to understand and easy to check. It comes
          down to three things.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">What "Owning It" Actually Means</h2>
        <p class="body">
          A website you own is yours in three separate places. Miss any one of
          them and you don't fully own it.
        </p>
        <div class="cards">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">The code</h3>
            <p class="card__body">The blueprints for your site. When you have the code, any developer on earth can pick it up and work on it. No code, no leaving.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">The domain</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Your address, yourbusiness.com, registered in your name. It's how customers find you, and it should never sit in someone else's account.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">The hosting</h3>
            <p class="card__body">The lot your site lives on. When the hosting account is yours, your site stays up no matter who you do or don't pay.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">The Rental Trap</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Builders like Wix and Squarespace are easy to start with, and that's the
          hook. What they don't say loudly is that the site only exists inside their
          walls. You can't export it, you don't get the code, and the day you stop
          paying, it disappears; pages, forms, and all. You've been paying for
          years and you walk away with nothing but the logo you uploaded. Some
          agencies run the same play with a fancier invoice: they keep your site on
          their account and charge a monthly retainer you can't cancel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">How to Tell What You Actually Own</h2>
        <p class="body">
          You don't need to be technical to check. Ask whoever built or hosts your
          site these four questions, and listen for a straight answer.
        </p>
        <ul class="levers">
          <li><strong>Is my domain in my name?</strong> Your email and your card on the registrar account, not theirs.</li>
          <li><strong>Can I get the code?</strong> If the answer is "it's on our platform," you don't own it.</li>
          <li><strong>Whose hosting account is the site on?</strong> It should be one you can log into.</li>
          <li><strong>If I leave tomorrow, what do I keep?</strong> The honest answer tells you everything.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--dark">
      <div class="section__container">
        <span class="overline overline--light">WHY IT MATTERS</span>
        <h2 class="h2 h2--light">Own It Like You Own Your Tools</h2>
        <p class="body body--light">
          When you own the code, the domain, and the hosting, you're free. You can
          hand the whole thing to another developer, move it, or just let it run
          for years without paying a soul. That's how I build; you get all three in
          your name and the keys in your hand. I'd rather you stay because the work
          keeps earning it than because you're locked in and can't leave. Your
          website should be like your truck and your tools: bought once, and yours.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--cta">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Not Sure What You Own? Let's Find Out.</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Tell me where your site lives now and I'll tell you straight what you
          actually own and what it would take to put it fully in your name. Book a
          free call; no pitch, no pressure, no obligation.
        </p>
        <div class="cta__actions">
          <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn--primary">Book a Free Call &rarr;</a>
          <a href="tel:+19093410243" class="btn btn--ghost">Or call 909-341-0243</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container section__container--narrow">
        <h2 class="h2">Common Questions About Owning a Website</h2>
        {faqs.map((f) => (
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq__q">{f.q}</summary>
            <p class="faq__a">{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="related">
      <div class="related__container">
        <p class="related__title">Keep Reading</p>
        <div class="related__grid">
          <a class="related__card" href="/small-business-website-cost/">
            <span>What Does a Small Business Website Cost?</span>
            <small>The four ways to buy one, and the rent-vs-own trap.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/missed-call-text-back/">
            <span>Missed-Call Text-Back</span>
            <small>Stop losing jobs to voicemail when you can't pick up.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/why-not-showing-on-google/">
            <span>Why Isn't My Business on Google?</span>
            <small>The usual reasons, and how to fix them.</small>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { background-color: var(--white); }
  .intro { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #1a1a2e 100%); padding: 72px 24px 64px; }
  .intro__container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .crumbs { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--tan); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .crumbs a { color: var(--copper-light); }
  .crumbs a:hover { color: var(--copper); }
  .overline { display: block; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .h1 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 3.6rem); line-height: 1.05; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .lede { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section--tint { background-color: var(--cream); }
  .section--dark { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--forest) 0%, #1a2a1c 100%); }
  .section--cta { background-color: var(--white); text-align: center; }
  .section__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section__container--narrow { max-width: 760px; }
  .h2 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .h2--light { color: var(--white); }
  .body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .body--light { color: var(--cream); }
  .body--gold { color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; }

  .cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px; }
  .card__title { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .card__body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .levers { list-style: none; margin-top: 12px; }
  .levers li { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.65; padding: 12px 0 12px 28px; position: relative; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cream); }
  .levers li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--copper-dark); font-weight: 700; }
  .levers strong { color: var(--navy); }

  .cta__actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; margin-top: 28px; }
  .btn { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; padding: 14px 26px; border-radius: 8px; transition: background-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease; }
  .btn--primary { background-color: var(--copper); color: var(--white); }
  .btn--primary:hover { background-color: #b8843f; }
  .btn--ghost { border: 1px solid var(--navy); color: var(--navy); }
  .btn--ghost:hover { background-color: var(--navy); color: var(--white); }
  .btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--copper); outline-offset: 2px; }

  .faq { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--tan); padding: 16px 0; }
  .faq__q { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.95rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; padding: 4px 0; }
  .faq__q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq__q::before { content: '+ '; font-weight: 700; }
  details[open] .faq__q::before { content: '− '; }
  .faq__a { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.7; padding: 12px 0 4px; }

  .related { background: var(--cream); padding: 48px 24px; }
  .related__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .related__title { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .related__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
  .related__card { display: block; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 18px; transition: border-color 0.2s ease; }
  .related__card:hover { border-color: var(--copper); }
  .related__card span { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3; }
  .related__card small { display: block; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5; }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .related__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
